Jan 12th, 2025 USDA unfortunately released a very bearish report for corn today that sent prices sharply lower. March corn closed 24 cents lower on the day. They increased harvested acres 1.3 million, increased yield 0.5 bpa to 186.5 bpa, both much higher than pre report expectations. Dec 1st stocks on hand also came in about 300 million more than expectations. Ending stocks were set at 2.227 billion, the highest in several years. The soybean numbers were more friendly, yield was unchanged from last month, and they cut exports which was mostly expected. This left ending stocks at 350 million, 25 million over last year. They did raise the Brazilian crop estimate on beans 3 million metric tons (110 million bushels), which was justified with their good growing conditions so far. It most likely takes a South American weather issue to rally the market now which is less likely on beans as Brazil will start harvesting soon, but they will plant most of their corn after that so there is some weather risk for the corn crop yet. Also Argentina has turned drier which is worth watching. Other than this a positive US biofuel policy which is expected to be released a some point fairly soon could help soybean demand as well.

name: Farm Service Cooperative
content:
Our Coop
Since 1930, when FSC began as a petroleum supply cooperative, this organization has been dedicated to providing essential resources for farmers and local consumers. Launching a company during the Great Depression and the Dust Bowl years wasn’t easy, but the cost efficiencies and service FSC offered allowed the fledgling company to survive. Back then, cooperative members banding together was still a novel concept.
Today’s farmers and consumers have good reason to consider the value of mutual investment every time they receive their dividend checks. Only a cooperative rewards its shareholders for also doing business with the company they own. And only a cooperative on a sound financial footing can reward patrons while consistently improving the services it offers.
FSC is not the largest cooperative in terms of widespread locations, yet it measures up against others in terms of return on investment. How does that happen? We remain true to the original FSC mandate to put knowledgeable, dedicated people into the field. The services they provide and the connections our employees form enable us to know what information, facilities, and equipment our customers expect from us today and, more importantly, what they’ll need us to provide in the years ahead.

name: Farmers Union Cooperative
content:
Products & Services
Grain
The grain team at Farmers Union Cooperative provides a strategic, forward-thinking approach to marketing that helps manage volatility and realize a better overall outcome from grain sales.
Feed
We’re big on service, expertise and choice, and we work with our patrons to find an optimal nutrition program that supports the productivity and health of their animals.
Agronomy
Our agronomy team has a reputation for serving farmers’ needs with expertise and understanding. We work closely with customers to determine their objectives, and we place a high emphasis on return on investment.
Seed
We represent Croplan and DEKALB/ASGROW seed brands, and we provide service and advice for all your seed needs. We focus on finding hybrids and varieties that yield best on your acres, while also providing characteristics like excellent dry down.
Propane
Whether you need propane for your home, farm or business, we’re here to help. Our team of professionals provide exceptional service and timely deliveries.
Energy
We serve northeast Iowa and southeast Minnesota with a full range of energy products, including propane, refined fuels, and engine lubricants and fluids.
Secure Financing Program
Operating loans from traditional ag lenders are based on financial factors, not yield potential. As a result, they often lend only up to the amount of insured production for operating loans, which can leave you short the dollars needed to farm most profitably.
Talk to us for more information on this farmer-focused financing option.
Find Your Career
We offer a positive, supportive culture with a path for career growth and new challenges. Find out what rewarding opportunities Farmers Union Cooperative has to offer for you.
Farmers Union Cooperative is a leading provider of propane for northeastern Iowa and southeastern Minnesota. Whether you need propane for your home, farm or business, we’re here to help.
Our team of professionals provide exceptional service and timely deliveries. We invest in ongoing training, and our technicians are certified by the state associations to complete inspections.
We service and install propane equipment and lines outside the building. When we conduct a safety check, we also go into the building to see what appliances are in use and if they meet code. But we do not provide service inside the home or business.
Please contact one of our three locations for more information on our services or to order propane.
Who we are
Farmers Union Cooperative proudly serves more than 1,500 members and 5,500-plus customers. It is our goal every day to adapt and grow to meet the growing needs of our patrons and customers. And we’ve done so through new technology, expanded scope, and added expertise.
Going forward, we will continue to invest in our employees and new technologies to better support our patrons and streamline our capabilities and service. Farmers Union truly reflects the cooperative spirit of working together, and we’ve done so for more than a century. This philosophy will hold true well into the next century as well!

We are a farmer-owned agricultural supply cooperative based in New Hampton, Iowa that proudly serves rural communities across Northern Iowa and Southern Minnesota. Visit our Country Store in New Hampton for a wide range of farm and home supplies. From garden tools to pet feed, LP tank refills to pond stocking—we have the products you use every day, all in one place. We stake the claim that we are North Iowa’s largest sprayer parts supplier.
We understand the financial needs of farmers. With in-house financing through RateStar, you get low-interest loans for seed, fertilizer, fuel, LP, and other crop inputs. Enjoy easy applications, payment flexibility, and savings compared to traditional lenders built specifically for agricultural production.
Our success starts with our team. We invest in people through training, support, and a strong workplace culture. When we care for our team members, they deliver the outstanding service our members expect.
Five Star is dedicated to supporting local schools, 4-H and FFA programs, fire departments, and other community efforts. We believe strong farms grow from strong communities.

content:
Brown Deer
Cooperative
BROWN DEER COOPERATIVE is a thoughtfully designed community offering active, independent adults age 55 or older an alternative to home ownership that is simple and secure. Situated on six scenic acres adjacent to the Brown Deer Golf Course, this exciting form of share ownership offers tax advantages, equity growth, a community lifestyle and freedom from the hassles of home maintenance responsibilities. As a shareholder at Brown Deer Cooperative, you play a part in the decision making of the day-to-day operations of the cooperative.
BROWN DEER COOPERATIVE
A housing cooperative is a form of joint ownership in a housing development. Members purchase a share in the cooperative. The cooperative holds title and owns the building and land. Members are a part of the cooperative and retain membership benefits through an occupancy agreement and through member participation.
OWNER
ELIGIBILITY
At least one owner of each home must be age 55 or above. All owners must qualify for membership and must show that they have the financial resources to purchase the membership share.
RETURN ON INVESTMENT
The value and share will appreciate using the Limited Equity Formula, limiting appreciation to 2.5% of the share value, compounded annually. This practice is widely used by cooperatives to keep the units affordable overtime, therefore building waiting lists of prospective buyers and to promote ease of resale.
